    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "FLY THE PACIFIC\nCANADA-USA-HAWAII\nFIJI-AUSTRALIA-NEW ZEALAND\nConnecting at San Francisco \u0026 Vancouver\nwith services to England and Europe\nwith\nВСРА\nFlying the sleeper equipped Douglas\nNON C6\nTimetable and Fares\nEffective from October 1, 1949. All previous lists cancelled.",
      "etc.\nreading\nclothes rack,\nwindow,\nEach\nsleeper\nown\nCall your local\ntravel\nagent or\nGeneral Agents\nAUSTRALIA:\nT.A.A.,\n339\nSwanston\nOffices\nStat\nMelbourne,\nC1.\nNEW ZEALAND\nall states.\nFIJI: N.Z.N.A.C., Mercantile Chambers,\nAuckland.\nAgencies throughout N.Z.\nHonolulu 2.\nU.S.A.:\nB.C.P.A.\nBooking\nOffice,\n347\nStockton\nSt.,\nSan\nFrancisco.\nPhone YUkon\n6-6971.\nB.O.A.C.:\nNew\nYork,\n420\nMadison\nAve.,\nNew\nYork\n17, N.Y.\nAlso\nCHICAGO, LOS\nANGELES,\nWASHINGTON.\nCANADA: T.C.A., Hotel Vancouver, B.C. Offices major cities.\nU.K. and elsewhere: B.O.A.C.\nB.C.P.A. HEAD OFFICE: A.P.A. Building, 53 Martin Place\nSydney. Phone BW 2741\n(15 lines).\nSAN\nFRANCISCO:\n347\nStockton\nPhone YUkon 6-6971.\nSt.\nSan\nFrancisco.\nel-\nwriting,\nmeals,\neach\nseat\nfor\nPrinted in Australia\ntable\nis\na handy\nThere"
